00:16:31.762 --> 00:16:33.264
[♪ unsettling, tense music playing]

00:16:34.473 --> 00:16:38.436
We just rented an abandoned building
and did some simple Photoshop work.

00:16:38.936 --> 00:16:40.229
We never purchased the land.

00:16:45.735 --> 00:16:46.736
It was...

00:16:48.612 --> 00:16:49.989
all fake?

00:16:51.907 --> 00:16:52.950
Then,

00:16:54.076 --> 00:16:55.995
what about the money we've wired?

00:16:56.078 --> 00:16:58.998
If you've seen Mr. Ko's report,
you should've known

00:16:59.790 --> 00:17:01.667
that the money was siphoned off.

00:17:03.919 --> 00:17:07.673
Through J Consulting,
that money is now in my pocket.

00:17:09.342 --> 00:17:12.428
J Consulting is my company.

00:17:15.765 --> 00:17:16.974
[breath trembling]

00:17:20.561 --> 00:17:21.562
I...

00:17:22.730 --> 00:17:24.190
I had my doubts, but...

00:17:26.442 --> 00:17:27.526
Then, [sniffles]

00:17:28.235 --> 00:17:32.740
since David was introduced to us
through J Consulting,

00:17:34.116 --> 00:17:36.160
is the fake contract

00:17:37.620 --> 00:17:38.829
also your doing?

00:17:40.915 --> 00:17:41.916
That's right.

00:17:43.042 --> 00:17:44.835
Why would you do that?

00:17:45.795 --> 00:17:49.799
How are you going to face
Miyeon and Eungsoo?

00:17:50.174 --> 00:17:52.635
[hums thoughtfully]
I don't think I'll need to see them again.

00:17:52.718 --> 00:17:53.886
[laughs smugly]

00:17:54.762 --> 00:17:57.640
You should've just given me
a section of the company.

00:17:57.723 --> 00:17:59.809
After dumping your
pathetic daughter on me,

00:17:59.892 --> 00:18:02.186
have you had no conscience?
[clicks tongue]

00:18:02.269 --> 00:18:04.021
You only gave me a bit of inheritance,

00:18:04.105 --> 00:18:05.898
like I'm some beggar.
[clicks tongue]

00:18:05.981 --> 00:18:07.650
What? [wheezing]

00:18:07.983 --> 00:18:08.984
You...

00:18:09.694 --> 00:18:11.946
You bastard! [gasping, grunts]

00:18:15.241 --> 00:18:16.325
[thuds]

00:18:17.284 --> 00:18:18.744
[♪ music increases in tempo]

00:18:25.042 --> 00:18:26.669
[breathing heavily]

00:18:29.797 --> 00:18:31.549
The medicine's not working, is it?

00:18:34.218 --> 00:18:35.720
[♪ ominous sting]

00:18:40.891 --> 00:18:41.892
[sighs]

00:18:42.226 --> 00:18:43.561
[♪ ominous music playing]

00:18:53.654 --> 00:18:55.197
[Philnyun breathing heavily]

00:18:55.614 --> 00:18:57.283
[Hangu] You'll lose
your consciousness soon.

00:18:57.366 --> 00:19:00.244
Because of your chronic illness,
it'll be ruled as a natural death.

00:19:00.327 --> 00:19:02.246
Well, maybe it's for the best.

00:19:03.539 --> 00:19:05.124
Rather than seeing the company

00:19:05.207 --> 00:19:08.544
you gave your life to
get broken up and sold in pieces,

00:19:09.044 --> 00:19:10.880
isn't it better that you go before then?

00:19:10.963 --> 00:19:12.381
[wheezing]

00:19:17.052 --> 00:19:18.345
[Philnyun continues wheezing]

00:19:21.307 --> 00:19:22.516
[mumbles shakily]

00:19:24.185 --> 00:19:25.269
[gasps]

00:19:28.522 --> 00:19:30.149
[♪ music increases in tempo]

00:19:49.877 --> 00:19:51.629
[♪ music crescendos, fades]

00:19:53.506 --> 00:19:55.508
[♪ ominous sting]

00:19:57.259 --> 00:19:59.428
[Miyeon] Where is she?

00:20:00.471 --> 00:20:01.806
-Which room?
-Slow down.

00:20:01.889 --> 00:20:03.057
No one's picking up.

00:20:03.140 --> 00:20:04.934
[angrily] Why aren't they picking up
their phone?

00:20:05.017 --> 00:20:07.019
[Eungsoo] Seriously,
why aren't they picking up?

00:20:07.102 --> 00:20:08.938
-[Miyeon breathing heavily]
-Slow down.

00:20:10.105 --> 00:20:14.735
Luckily, she survived,
but she's barely responsive.

00:20:14.819 --> 00:20:16.821
The surgery went well,

00:20:16.904 --> 00:20:20.574
but because of her age
and chronic illness,

00:20:20.658 --> 00:20:23.786
at this point,
there's very little chance she'll wake up.

00:20:23.869 --> 00:20:28.207
Are you saying
Mom's just going to stay like this?

00:20:28.290 --> 00:20:29.875
She'll never wake up?

00:20:29.959 --> 00:20:33.045
When she came to the hospital,
she was already unconscious.

00:20:33.128 --> 00:20:34.797
[breath trembling]

00:20:36.590 --> 00:20:38.425
What were you doing, Ms. Kim?

00:20:38.509 --> 00:20:41.178
Where the hell were you,
leaving Mom all alone?

00:20:41.262 --> 00:20:42.555
What were you doing?

00:20:43.305 --> 00:20:44.807
I'm sorry. [sniffling]

00:20:45.224 --> 00:20:46.767
I was only out for a moment.

00:20:47.726 --> 00:20:48.727
Calm down.

00:20:48.811 --> 00:20:50.646
She's been ill for a while.

00:20:50.729 --> 00:20:52.439
[breathing heavily]

00:20:52.523 --> 00:20:55.860
She was fine
when I stopped by in the evening.

00:20:55.943 --> 00:20:57.486
[Miyeon] Oh, what do we do?

00:20:57.570 --> 00:20:59.572
What if my mom dies?

00:21:00.197 --> 00:21:01.532
Is there no other way

00:21:02.283 --> 00:21:04.243
than to just wait for her to wake up?

00:21:04.326 --> 00:21:06.620
[Dr. Yoon] Our priority is to stop
additional brain hemorrhage

00:21:06.704 --> 00:21:08.998
and to control her intracranial pressure.

00:21:09.623 --> 00:21:10.958
If bleeding reoccurs,

00:21:11.959 --> 00:21:12.960
she won't survive.

00:21:13.335 --> 00:21:14.420
[sighs]

00:21:15.087 --> 00:21:17.256
[Miyeon sobbing] Oh, no. Mom...

00:21:17.339 --> 00:21:19.091
[♪ tense, melancholy music playing]

00:21:19.216 --> 00:21:20.342
Mom...

00:21:25.139 --> 00:21:26.724
[Miyeon continues sobbing]

00:21:38.485 --> 00:21:39.486
[sighs softly]

00:21:41.238 --> 00:21:42.281
[line ringing]

00:21:45.492 --> 00:21:47.244
[♪ tense, foreboding music playing]

00:21:47.328 --> 00:21:48.329
Let's begin.

00:21:50.915 --> 00:21:51.916
[line disconnects]

00:21:56.128 --> 00:21:57.463
[sighs in relief]

00:21:58.923 --> 00:22:01.467
[news anchor over TV] Myungsoondang,
a bakery with an 80-year history,

00:22:01.550 --> 00:22:04.136
is under suspicion
of having received a large investment

00:22:04.219 --> 00:22:07.139
from an investment firm
through a falsified supply contract.

00:22:07.222 --> 00:22:11.685
Using a fake supply contract
with the global hotel Kaltz as collateral,

00:22:11.769 --> 00:22:14.563
Myungsoondang reportedly obtained

00:22:14.647 --> 00:22:18.025
an investment of 30 billion won
from BQ Capital, a US-based firm.

00:22:18.108 --> 00:22:20.444
Myungsoondang won
the President's Award this year

00:22:20.527 --> 00:22:22.404
for its outstanding
social contributions...

00:22:24.239 --> 00:22:25.366
[Miyeon sighs deeply]

00:22:25.449 --> 00:22:28.535
Mom was deceived.
You know what she's like.

00:22:28.619 --> 00:22:31.413
She would never go astray.

00:22:31.497 --> 00:22:33.248
Forged a contract?

00:22:33.791 --> 00:22:35.000
-[breathing heavily] Geez.
-Mom...

00:22:36.418 --> 00:22:39.880
Shouldn't we catch this David guy first?

00:22:39.964 --> 00:22:44.134
We should request an investigation
to catch this guy so that...

00:22:44.218 --> 00:22:45.803
It's no use. [sighs]

00:22:47.012 --> 00:22:48.305
It's still a fact

00:22:48.389 --> 00:22:51.475
that the chairwoman obtained
the investment through a fake contract.

00:22:52.476 --> 00:22:55.896
[sighs] I should've tried harder
to stop her.

00:22:56.397 --> 00:22:58.023
But is it actually true?

00:22:59.274 --> 00:23:00.651
Ms. Kim said

00:23:01.235 --> 00:23:03.779
Grandma met with David up until recently.

00:23:04.279 --> 00:23:06.115
Wasn't it to discuss the supply plan?

00:23:07.866 --> 00:23:10.494
She met with him for a different reason.

00:23:11.161 --> 00:23:12.788
To ask him to keep it a secret

00:23:12.871 --> 00:23:15.249
from the investors
that the contract was put on hold.

00:23:15.332 --> 00:23:16.709
[♪ suspenseful music playing]

00:23:16.792 --> 00:23:17.876
[Hangu sighs softly]

00:23:21.296 --> 00:23:23.173
MARKETING TEAM

00:23:23.257 --> 00:23:25.926
[Hangu] In her first year as Chairwoman,

00:23:26.510 --> 00:23:28.554
our operating profit was cut in half.

00:23:29.555 --> 00:23:31.181
Revenue held steady,

00:23:31.932 --> 00:23:34.476
but turning all the part-timers
into full-time employees

00:23:34.560 --> 00:23:36.353
sent labor costs through the roof.

00:23:36.937 --> 00:23:39.314
And after losing the lawsuit
over the logistics hub,

00:23:39.398 --> 00:23:40.691
we sank deeper into deficit.

00:23:41.900 --> 00:23:45.612
By forging the Kaltz Hotel contract,
which was still being negotiated,

00:23:45.696 --> 00:23:47.698
she told me
to secure the investment first.

00:23:48.323 --> 00:23:50.159
By putting out the fire,

00:23:50.993 --> 00:23:54.246
I think she meant to get the contract
signed in the meantime.

00:23:55.080 --> 00:23:56.123
[sighs]

00:23:58.333 --> 00:23:59.334
All this time,

00:24:01.128 --> 00:24:03.380
she's been struggling on her own.

00:24:05.007 --> 00:24:06.592
MS. KIM

00:24:10.429 --> 00:24:11.597
[phone vibrating]

00:24:13.474 --> 00:24:15.851
[♪ soft jazz music playing in background]

00:24:20.689 --> 00:24:22.649
You could've just come to my office.

00:24:26.070 --> 00:24:28.280
I have something to tell you privately.

00:24:30.491 --> 00:24:35.704
The chairwoman probably didn't know
that the contract with the Kaltz was fake.

00:24:36.955 --> 00:24:37.998
What?

00:24:38.082 --> 00:24:39.291
The day she collapsed,

00:24:39.917 --> 00:24:42.419
she asked me to look into David.

00:24:43.378 --> 00:24:45.172
[♪ soft, melancholy music playing]

00:24:50.886 --> 00:24:52.638
[Juhee] If she knew
it was a fake contract,

00:24:53.097 --> 00:24:55.641
why would she ask me to look into him?

00:24:56.350 --> 00:24:58.310
She didn't even know he had been fired.

00:25:20.082 --> 00:25:21.583
[Philnyun] It doesn't feel right.

00:25:22.084 --> 00:25:26.547
I'd like you to look into it
without Director Jang knowing.

00:25:31.552 --> 00:25:32.553
Grandma.

00:25:33.220 --> 00:25:34.638
I'm afraid.

00:25:40.978 --> 00:25:42.604
I'm afraid that you were right.

00:25:45.357 --> 00:25:46.358
BULLETIN BOARD

00:25:47.985 --> 00:25:50.654
SO MUCH FOR BEING
A SOCIALLY RESPONSIBLE COMPANY

00:25:50.737 --> 00:25:52.406
[Songhee sighing]
It's getting really messy.

00:25:52.489 --> 00:25:54.825
People are already starting a boycott.

00:25:54.908 --> 00:25:56.326
RETURN THE PRESIDENT'S AWARD!

00:25:56.410 --> 00:25:57.995
[♪ melancholy music continues]

00:26:17.514 --> 00:26:18.640
Mr. Kim.

00:26:28.650 --> 00:26:30.611
Did you have dinner?

00:26:31.195 --> 00:26:33.697
[sighs wearily]
I don't have much appetite.

00:26:34.072 --> 00:26:36.450
Anyway, what brings you by?

00:26:36.533 --> 00:26:37.743
What do you think?

00:26:37.826 --> 00:26:40.787
-I came to hear you sigh.
-[chuckles softly]

00:26:41.830 --> 00:26:43.123
Seriously.

00:26:43.957 --> 00:26:48.086
When things are hard,
they say it helps to take three big sighs.

00:26:48.170 --> 00:26:49.213
Nonsense.

00:26:49.296 --> 00:26:51.006
I'm serious. Try it.

00:26:51.798 --> 00:26:52.799
Go on.

00:26:55.761 --> 00:26:56.803
[sighs]

00:26:57.262 --> 00:26:58.305
[sighs softly]

00:26:58.764 --> 00:27:00.307
You must be really concerned.

00:27:00.390 --> 00:27:01.934
[sighs, chuckles]

00:27:02.309 --> 00:27:04.269
I can tell from your sighs.

00:27:04.353 --> 00:27:05.520
[acknowledges]

00:27:05.771 --> 00:27:07.940
-[sighs]
-You feel a little bit better, right?

00:27:08.732 --> 00:27:09.733
Mmm-hmm.

00:27:09.816 --> 00:27:12.277
You can tell me about anything.

00:27:12.361 --> 00:27:16.365
I'll listen with one ear
and let it out the other.

00:27:19.910 --> 00:27:21.119
[hums thoughtfully]

00:27:22.704 --> 00:27:23.830
[clicks tongue]

00:27:29.836 --> 00:27:30.879
[sighs softly]

00:27:31.630 --> 00:27:32.631
[Meri in English] Okay.

00:27:33.298 --> 00:27:35.676
[Meri singing in Korean]
♪ I want to know ♪

00:27:35.759 --> 00:27:40.806
♪ Even the smallest things about you ♪

00:27:40.889 --> 00:27:43.141
♪ But for some reason ♪

00:27:43.225 --> 00:27:47.479
♪ You don't tell me ♪

00:27:48.188 --> 00:27:49.690
[♪ soft, gentle music playing]

00:27:51.566 --> 00:27:54.069
Gosh, if I were you, I would've told you.

00:27:55.237 --> 00:27:56.279
Fine, I will.

00:27:58.573 --> 00:28:00.367
-Shall we take a walk?
-Sure.

00:28:05.914 --> 00:28:08.583
So, you're suspicious
of your uncle right now, right?

00:28:09.584 --> 00:28:13.672
I had my doubts even when she asked me
to look into J Consulting.

00:28:15.340 --> 00:28:17.968
I couldn't even ask him.

00:28:18.051 --> 00:28:19.678
Of course not.

00:28:20.095 --> 00:28:23.348
You said he was like a father to you.

00:28:23.974 --> 00:28:26.685
It's not like there's solid proof yet.

00:28:27.144 --> 00:28:30.188
I just know that he's lying.

00:28:30.605 --> 00:28:32.399
Then you should reveal the truth.

00:28:33.442 --> 00:28:36.194
When someone you trust betrays you,

00:28:36.278 --> 00:28:37.654
at first,

00:28:37.738 --> 00:28:42.075
you start wondering why they lied to you.

00:28:42.159 --> 00:28:43.994
Then you start blaming yourself.

00:28:44.995 --> 00:28:47.622
You start wondering
what you've done wrong,

00:28:47.706 --> 00:28:49.583
and when it started going wrong.

00:28:50.375 --> 00:28:53.420
But if you think about it again,

00:28:53.503 --> 00:28:55.213
it's not because you did something.

00:28:56.006 --> 00:28:57.841
The person who betrayed you is at fault.

00:28:59.009 --> 00:29:02.054
So, if your uncle is lying
about something,

00:29:02.137 --> 00:29:03.472
you should reveal it.

00:29:05.015 --> 00:29:06.641
Before he does something worse.

00:29:09.061 --> 00:29:11.021
Aren't you going to save Myungsoondang?

00:29:11.104 --> 00:29:12.606
That's what the successor is for.

00:29:12.689 --> 00:29:14.066
No one else can do this but you.

00:29:16.902 --> 00:29:19.237
Don't think too much.

00:29:20.238 --> 00:29:22.491
Just do what you can do right now.

00:29:22.574 --> 00:29:24.284
[♪ gentle, poignant music playing]

00:29:26.078 --> 00:29:29.414
If someone gives you a hard time,
I won't stand for it.

00:29:29.498 --> 00:29:30.540
[chuckles]

00:29:39.508 --> 00:29:40.592
Thank you.

00:30:05.075 --> 00:30:08.286
[Meri] If someone gives you a hard time,
I won't stand for it.

00:30:43.989 --> 00:30:45.073
[sighs]

00:30:57.419 --> 00:30:59.087
[♪ soft jazz music
playing in background]

00:31:01.298 --> 00:31:02.299
You're here.

00:31:02.382 --> 00:31:04.050
Would you like the same drink?

00:31:04.134 --> 00:31:05.302
Yes, please.

00:31:05.385 --> 00:31:06.428
Okay.

00:31:14.519 --> 00:31:16.646
At least say hi.

00:31:17.606 --> 00:31:19.065
We do share a secret after all.

00:31:19.774 --> 00:31:21.693
Isn't it better
to pretend to be strangers?

00:31:21.776 --> 00:31:23.111
I'm sure that'd be better.

00:31:23.486 --> 00:31:25.113
You think so?

00:31:27.407 --> 00:31:30.243
Anyway, thank you
for accepting my suggestion.

00:31:30.327 --> 00:31:33.205
I'm still thinking about it.
Don't get ahead of yourself.

00:31:33.747 --> 00:31:35.624
Is your boss still pressuring you?

00:31:35.707 --> 00:31:38.501
Play him my recording,
then he won't say another word.

00:31:38.585 --> 00:31:40.420
Then he'll pull the hospital's funding.

00:31:41.087 --> 00:31:42.923
Wow, how petty.

00:31:43.006 --> 00:31:44.382
That's the world of business.

00:31:51.431 --> 00:31:52.432
I don't get it.

00:31:54.768 --> 00:31:56.811
Why are you going to such lengths?

00:31:57.270 --> 00:31:59.773
You said Mr. Kim
doesn't see you as a woman.

00:32:00.857 --> 00:32:01.983
Mr. Baek.

00:32:03.526 --> 00:32:05.779
You've never
truly liked someone, have you?

00:32:06.321 --> 00:32:08.406
You want them to do well.

00:32:08.949 --> 00:32:10.867
You want to protect them.

00:32:10.951 --> 00:32:12.786
You feel their pain as if it's your own.

00:32:13.536 --> 00:32:16.748
There's no reason behind it,
no matter how much you try to find one.

00:32:16.831 --> 00:32:18.166
It's an automatic response.

00:32:20.335 --> 00:32:22.587
Still, it's not like he'll even notice.

00:32:22.671 --> 00:32:24.839
Stop hitting me with the hard truth.

00:32:25.632 --> 00:32:28.343
Even if he doesn't notice,
it doesn't matter, okay?

00:32:33.431 --> 00:32:34.432
[sighs softly]

00:32:35.392 --> 00:32:36.935
I'm sorry if I offended you.

00:32:37.018 --> 00:32:40.522
Because you heard a thing about me,

00:32:41.606 --> 00:32:42.691
I got a bit...

00:32:43.900 --> 00:32:45.193
sensitive.

00:32:45.277 --> 00:32:46.319
[exclaims quizzically]

00:32:46.695 --> 00:32:47.862
Heard what?

00:32:49.990 --> 00:32:51.658
Did I hear something?

00:32:53.326 --> 00:32:54.828
I don't care. You sort it out.

00:32:56.079 --> 00:32:58.456
Hey, do it like you blackmailed
my dad into paying

00:32:58.540 --> 00:33:01.293
to send you abroad to study
because you took an exam for me.

00:33:01.376 --> 00:33:03.169
You used to be quick on your feet.

00:33:03.253 --> 00:33:05.213
Why have you lost your touch?

00:33:06.131 --> 00:33:08.049
Has life been a little too good for you?

00:33:10.510 --> 00:33:11.678
Nothing.

00:33:11.761 --> 00:33:15.640
You know, people aren't really
interested in how you've lived.

00:33:16.683 --> 00:33:20.103
So, stop acting all guilty like that.

00:33:20.186 --> 00:33:22.355
[stutters] I don't feel guilty.

00:33:22.439 --> 00:33:25.942
I think you do,
[mockingly] judging by your stutter.

00:33:26.735 --> 00:33:27.861
[chuckles softly]

00:33:28.611 --> 00:33:29.612
[Jingyeong chuckles]

00:33:30.155 --> 00:33:31.156
[chuckles]

00:33:31.531 --> 00:33:32.782
[chuckles]

00:33:34.909 --> 00:33:38.913
If you received a favor,
just repay them exactly what you owe.

00:33:38.997 --> 00:33:40.915
I think anything beyond that is excessive.

00:33:42.500 --> 00:33:44.127
You know,

00:33:45.128 --> 00:33:48.006
you act all high and mighty,
but you're a bit of a fool.

00:33:48.882 --> 00:33:52.385
I guess I don't really know
how much you owe them,

00:33:52.469 --> 00:33:56.014
but haven't you worked hard enough
that it's all been paid off?

00:33:56.514 --> 00:33:58.308
Then you don't need to do any more.

00:33:58.391 --> 00:33:59.851
In my opinion,

00:34:00.810 --> 00:34:03.521
compared to your boss,
the one who pretended to be ill,

00:34:03.605 --> 00:34:07.108
you're a hundred,
a thousand times smarter.

00:34:07.650 --> 00:34:10.487
So, you don't need
to keep putting up with it.

00:34:10.570 --> 00:34:11.821
Actually,

00:34:12.572 --> 00:34:13.823
you've got what it takes.

00:34:14.366 --> 00:34:16.868
The way I see it, you're quite all right.

00:34:18.370 --> 00:34:20.622
What, do you want me
to find you another job?

00:34:20.705 --> 00:34:21.873
[chuckles softly]

00:34:22.832 --> 00:34:23.917
[inhales deeply]

00:34:51.986 --> 00:34:53.029
INVESTMENT CONTRACT

00:35:08.461 --> 00:35:09.671
Article 8, Clause 3.

00:35:10.797 --> 00:35:13.258
Instead of paying the penalty for breach,

00:35:13.842 --> 00:35:16.553
it says BQ Capital can take part
in management.

00:35:16.636 --> 00:35:18.555
That's the clause you should point out.

00:35:18.638 --> 00:35:22.142
So, the justification is
to speed up the investment rounds?

00:35:22.225 --> 00:35:24.185
With the penalty,
it's about 60 billion won.

00:35:24.269 --> 00:35:26.479
That's about a 35-percent stake.

00:35:26.563 --> 00:35:28.022
With that, we can change bylaws,

00:35:28.106 --> 00:35:30.775
appoint directors,
or approve mergers and acquisitions.

00:35:32.444 --> 00:35:35.864
Once we take management control,
I'm going to sell the company in pieces.

00:35:37.741 --> 00:35:38.742
[in English] Okay.

00:35:42.078 --> 00:35:44.497
[in Korean] Before all that,
there's something

00:35:45.248 --> 00:35:46.916
I want to confirm with you.

00:35:47.625 --> 00:35:48.710
[chuckles softly]

00:36:06.436 --> 00:36:07.979
MUTUAL DIVORCE CONFIRMATION FORM

00:36:08.062 --> 00:36:09.272
APPLICANT JANG HANGU

00:36:09.856 --> 00:36:10.857
[chuckles softly]

00:36:10.940 --> 00:36:12.525
[♪ gripping, tense music playing]

00:36:19.532 --> 00:36:20.742
[Hangu chuckles softly]

00:36:22.994 --> 00:36:24.287
[gulps, sighs]

00:36:26.706 --> 00:36:27.832
[sighs in relief]

00:36:32.212 --> 00:36:34.005
HUSBAND JANG HANGU

00:36:45.016 --> 00:36:46.267
[sighs wearily]

00:36:46.768 --> 00:36:49.270
I can't get any work done
with all this chaos.

00:36:49.813 --> 00:36:51.981
[sighs wearily]
Tell me about it.

00:36:52.065 --> 00:36:53.608
I'D LIKE TO LEAVE THE SHOW...

00:36:53.691 --> 00:36:54.776
PRODUCER OF I AM SINGLE

00:36:54.859 --> 00:36:55.860
[Ms. Oh] What will you do?

00:36:56.861 --> 00:36:59.280
-Pardon?
-The company is about to be sold off.

00:36:59.364 --> 00:37:00.615
There's no time to relax.

00:37:02.575 --> 00:37:03.660
[sighs]

00:37:03.743 --> 00:37:05.995
That's why I withdrew.

00:37:06.371 --> 00:37:07.372
Withdrew from what?

00:37:08.039 --> 00:37:10.667
I feel like people will just talk
if I'm on the show.

00:37:11.042 --> 00:37:12.961
I just texted them that I'm stepping down

00:37:13.044 --> 00:37:15.171
from the show due to personal reasons.

00:37:15.255 --> 00:37:17.507
I wasn't asking you about I Am Single.

00:37:18.132 --> 00:37:20.552
There's a rumor going around

00:37:20.635 --> 00:37:23.012
that BQ Capital
will be running our company.

00:37:23.096 --> 00:37:24.556
Oh, that.

00:37:25.139 --> 00:37:26.224
[scoffs]

00:37:26.307 --> 00:37:28.059
I believe in our company.

00:37:28.142 --> 00:37:31.229
If it was going to fall just like this,
I wouldn't have worked here.

00:37:31.312 --> 00:37:33.731
Actually, me too.

00:37:33.815 --> 00:37:35.108
We're on the same page.

00:37:36.442 --> 00:37:37.569
[groans softly]

00:37:37.652 --> 00:37:39.362
[sighing] So naive.

00:37:39.821 --> 00:37:42.532
Start writing up a new resume.

00:37:42.615 --> 00:37:44.868
You should move while you're still young.

00:37:44.951 --> 00:37:47.245
Once you're older,
not many places will hire you.

00:37:49.163 --> 00:37:53.459
[Ms. Oh] Of course, there will be layoffs
once the ownership changes.

00:37:53.543 --> 00:37:55.628
You should be looking for a job now.

00:37:55.712 --> 00:37:58.214
You haven't worked for five years.
Have some conscience.

00:37:58.798 --> 00:38:00.341
What? A house-husband?

00:38:00.425 --> 00:38:02.510
Hey, I'm the one who cooks,

00:38:02.594 --> 00:38:03.803
pays for our child,

00:38:03.887 --> 00:38:05.680
and nurses your mom, you jerk.

00:38:05.763 --> 00:38:07.098
Just hang up! Geez.

00:38:07.181 --> 00:38:08.266
[line disconnects]

00:38:09.267 --> 00:38:10.435
[sighs in exasperation]

00:38:11.728 --> 00:38:14.147
I might actually be laid off at this rate.

00:38:15.064 --> 00:38:16.065
What do I do?

00:38:16.733 --> 00:38:18.026
[♪ melancholy music playing]

00:38:19.736 --> 00:38:20.737
[sighs]

00:38:24.866 --> 00:38:26.242
[sighs in despair]

00:38:27.327 --> 00:38:28.703
EXPECTED BQ RESPONSE

00:38:29.913 --> 00:38:33.249
BQ NEGOTIATION RESPONSE PLAN

00:38:33.917 --> 00:38:35.418
MEASURES AGAINST MASS LAYOFFS

00:38:38.796 --> 00:38:40.673
It suddenly hit me

00:38:41.049 --> 00:38:44.844
that these people's future
all depends on this agreement.

00:38:45.637 --> 00:38:47.972
[sighs] I really need to do well.

00:38:50.767 --> 00:38:51.893
When Grandma was around,

00:38:51.976 --> 00:38:54.270
the weight of responsibility
didn't feel so heavy.

00:38:54.354 --> 00:38:55.813
Of course.

00:38:55.897 --> 00:38:58.066
Did you think you'd go down alone?

00:38:59.108 --> 00:39:01.027
It'll be the end for the employees,

00:39:01.110 --> 00:39:02.612
and for my company, too.

00:39:02.695 --> 00:39:05.114
Myungsoondang is a huge client for me.

00:39:06.074 --> 00:39:08.660
That's why I'm here.
To see if you're doing a good job.

00:39:11.371 --> 00:39:12.455
Do you know

00:39:13.164 --> 00:39:15.875
when I'm most excited
and when it's the hardest for me?

00:39:17.543 --> 00:39:18.962
The payday.

00:39:19.712 --> 00:39:20.880
I know,

00:39:21.297 --> 00:39:23.633
my company is small
with only one employee.

00:39:23.716 --> 00:39:25.134
[♪ poignant music playing]

00:39:25.218 --> 00:39:26.886
But when we have no work that month,

00:39:26.970 --> 00:39:30.348
the approaching payday is frightening.

00:39:31.808 --> 00:39:34.102
I feel like I live to pay my employee.

00:39:34.185 --> 00:39:35.353
Work-life balance?

00:39:35.436 --> 00:39:36.562
What's that?

00:39:37.897 --> 00:39:40.900
Even if I feel like I'm about to collapse
from working all night,

00:39:40.984 --> 00:39:43.152
after paying my employee on time,

00:39:43.236 --> 00:39:45.238
I feel so proud.

00:39:46.948 --> 00:39:49.200
It feels like
I'm keeping a promise to people

00:39:49.283 --> 00:39:50.994
who trusted me and worked with me.

00:39:53.579 --> 00:39:56.165
After feeling such responsibility,

00:39:57.583 --> 00:40:01.129
I think I've become an adult.

00:40:03.423 --> 00:40:04.632
I'll keep trying.

00:40:08.803 --> 00:40:09.846
[sighs softly]

00:40:11.222 --> 00:40:13.516
I hope it goes well
with the investor tomorrow.

00:40:14.392 --> 00:40:16.644
If you can't pay the penalty,

00:40:17.937 --> 00:40:20.314
they'll probably take over
management, right?

00:40:20.398 --> 00:40:21.399
Yes.

00:40:22.358 --> 00:40:24.569
They'll most likely begin with layoffs.

00:40:24.652 --> 00:40:25.737
So, I'm worried.

00:40:26.154 --> 00:40:28.072
I have to stop that at all costs.

00:40:28.156 --> 00:40:30.199
What's the CEO of BQ Capital like?

00:40:33.619 --> 00:40:34.746
Her name is Sylvia.

00:40:34.829 --> 00:40:36.164
She's a Korean American.

00:40:36.247 --> 00:40:38.332
But I don't know anything
apart from her name.

00:40:40.126 --> 00:40:41.127
This person...

00:40:42.670 --> 00:40:44.338
I've seen her somewhere.

00:40:46.632 --> 00:40:47.717
Oh, wait!

00:41:03.691 --> 00:41:04.942
Look at this.

00:41:05.526 --> 00:41:08.946
It's a photo from the farewell party
when Sori quit her restaurant.

00:41:09.947 --> 00:41:11.282
Isn't she the same person?

00:41:12.492 --> 00:41:13.743
[♪ tense music playing]

00:41:13.826 --> 00:41:14.911
[Kim Wooju] Who is she?

00:41:14.994 --> 00:41:17.413
[Meri] She's the owner of the restaurant.

00:41:17.497 --> 00:41:19.248
But her name is different.

00:41:19.332 --> 00:41:22.085
She said her name was Jessica, not Sylvia.

00:41:24.087 --> 00:41:25.213
Jessica?

00:41:25.630 --> 00:41:27.715
[John in English] Since the address
matches perfectly,

00:41:27.799 --> 00:41:30.885
I looked up if the owner
was the same person, and it was.

00:41:30.968 --> 00:41:32.386
Her name is Jessica.

00:41:33.930 --> 00:41:35.098
J Consulting America
COMPANY FINANCIALS

00:41:35.181 --> 00:41:36.682
CEO Jessica

00:41:37.809 --> 00:41:40.353
[Meri] Do you think she's a twin?

00:41:44.524 --> 00:41:45.942
MERI

00:41:48.778 --> 00:41:50.071
What's this?

00:41:51.197 --> 00:41:53.157
-[phone vibrates]
-[Meri] Is this your boss?

00:41:56.119 --> 00:41:57.286
[Sori] Yes, it is.

00:41:57.703 --> 00:41:59.163
Where did you get this photo?

00:42:00.540 --> 00:42:01.582
[line connects]

00:42:02.458 --> 00:42:03.501
SORI

00:42:03.584 --> 00:42:05.294
[Meri] Take a closer look at the photo.

00:42:05.378 --> 00:42:06.504
She's called Sylvia.

00:42:06.587 --> 00:42:07.880
Are you sure it's your boss?

00:42:07.964 --> 00:42:09.340
[Sori] I told you it's her.

00:42:09.757 --> 00:42:11.884
-She's not a twin?
-She's not.

00:42:11.968 --> 00:42:13.761
That's her husband right next to her.

00:42:13.845 --> 00:42:15.763
[♪ tense, gripping music playing]

00:42:15.847 --> 00:42:16.848
Her husband?

00:42:17.473 --> 00:42:18.933
How do you know? You saw him?

00:42:19.016 --> 00:42:20.143
Yeah.

00:42:20.226 --> 00:42:22.728
I saw him when I dropped
her son off from school.

00:42:26.482 --> 00:42:28.192
[Hangu and Henry chuckle]

00:42:28.276 --> 00:42:29.569
He's heavy.

00:42:32.488 --> 00:42:33.531
I'm certain.

00:42:36.117 --> 00:42:37.410
[Meri] Okay.

00:42:38.077 --> 00:42:39.120
Bye.

00:42:44.750 --> 00:42:47.295
He's your uncle, isn't he?

00:42:48.588 --> 00:42:49.589
He is.

00:42:50.131 --> 00:42:53.217
What do you think is going on here?

00:42:53.301 --> 00:42:54.677
I think...

00:42:56.345 --> 00:42:58.222
Sylvia and Jessica

00:42:59.891 --> 00:43:01.225
are the same person.

00:43:03.436 --> 00:43:04.687
But then...

00:43:06.856 --> 00:43:08.024
that means...

00:43:10.026 --> 00:43:14.280
your uncle's working with the people
who are trying to take over the company.

00:43:15.656 --> 00:43:17.533
That's highly likely.

00:43:20.119 --> 00:43:22.496
If David was also in on it...

00:43:31.005 --> 00:43:34.717
Then, do you think
your aunt knows all this?

00:43:35.384 --> 00:43:37.136
That he even has a son in the US.

00:43:42.892 --> 00:43:44.685
MYUNGSOONDANG

00:43:50.566 --> 00:43:52.235
MUTUAL DIVORCE CONFIRMATION FORM

00:43:52.318 --> 00:43:53.778
APPLICANT JANG HANGU

00:43:54.403 --> 00:43:55.404
[sighs]

00:43:58.115 --> 00:43:59.325
What are you doing here?

00:43:59.408 --> 00:44:00.409
What? Nothing.

00:44:00.868 --> 00:44:01.953
What is it?

00:44:02.036 --> 00:44:04.372
I need to go to the hospital to see Mom.

00:44:04.455 --> 00:44:05.957
Can you drive?

00:44:06.040 --> 00:44:07.416
I'm too exhausted right now.

00:44:07.500 --> 00:44:09.377
Okay.

00:44:24.475 --> 00:44:26.310
[♪ tense, foreboding music playing]

00:44:39.156 --> 00:44:40.616
Welcome, ma'am.

00:44:41.659 --> 00:44:43.911
It's been a while. How have you been?

00:44:43.995 --> 00:44:46.122
As you know, the company's a bit...

00:44:46.914 --> 00:44:48.207
[Jessica] I'm sorry to hear it.

00:44:48.291 --> 00:44:50.918
Let's all put our heads together
and find a solution.

00:44:51.002 --> 00:44:52.461
Of course.

00:44:52.545 --> 00:44:54.880
These are our team leaders
joining us today.

00:44:54.964 --> 00:44:56.590
They're the chairwoman's grandsons.

00:44:57.300 --> 00:44:59.760
I'm Sylvia Oh, the CEO of BQ Capital.

00:44:59.844 --> 00:45:00.928
[acknowledges]

00:45:02.013 --> 00:45:03.306
I'm Jang Eungsoo.

00:45:08.644 --> 00:45:09.937
I'm Kim Wooju.

00:45:13.733 --> 00:45:15.401
[♪ dramatic sting]

00:45:15.860 --> 00:45:16.861
[Hangu] Please sit.

00:45:27.997 --> 00:45:29.498
Employment security?

00:45:30.583 --> 00:45:31.667
[clicks tongue, scoffs]

00:45:32.084 --> 00:45:33.794
I think you're mistaken.

00:45:35.046 --> 00:45:37.006
We're not running a charity.

00:45:37.089 --> 00:45:38.174
We're investors.

00:45:38.257 --> 00:45:39.300
However,

00:45:39.800 --> 00:45:42.803
from factory workers
to delivery drivers and café staff.

00:45:42.887 --> 00:45:45.014
They're all full-time employees
at Myungsoondang.

00:45:45.097 --> 00:45:46.849
-So, layoffs can't be--
-If you can't,

00:45:46.932 --> 00:45:48.351
pay the penalty.

00:45:50.644 --> 00:45:51.645
[Eungsoo] Ma'am.

00:45:51.729 --> 00:45:54.690
[chuckles softly]
Please don't be so harsh.

00:45:54.774 --> 00:45:58.027
If you could give us a little time,
we'll come up with a solution.

00:45:58.110 --> 00:45:59.153
[Jessica chuckles softly]

00:45:59.987 --> 00:46:02.782
Sales are tanking
with public opinion turning sour,

00:46:02.865 --> 00:46:05.242
and your assets
are all tied up in real estate.

00:46:05.326 --> 00:46:07.620
I also heard you can't
get any extra loans.

00:46:08.371 --> 00:46:09.705
Isn't that right?

00:46:09.789 --> 00:46:11.165
So, what can you do?

00:46:13.042 --> 00:46:15.169
If you want to recover
at least the investment,

00:46:15.252 --> 00:46:17.380
you'll even have to sell
the company in pieces.

00:46:18.964 --> 00:46:20.007
Is that what you want?

00:46:20.091 --> 00:46:21.133
Ma'am...

00:46:21.217 --> 00:46:22.760
[♪ ominous music playing]

00:46:26.514 --> 00:46:27.598
[sighs softly]

00:46:28.682 --> 00:46:29.892
Okay.

00:46:32.520 --> 00:46:36.774
We'll first discuss among ourselves
regarding your requests.

00:46:43.864 --> 00:46:45.241
CFO
JANG HANGU

00:46:45.324 --> 00:46:47.493
How could you be so emotional?

00:46:47.576 --> 00:46:49.620
Nothing good will come from crossing her.

00:46:51.288 --> 00:46:52.415
But...

00:46:53.666 --> 00:46:55.918
[Meri] Let's see how your uncle reacts.

00:46:56.377 --> 00:46:58.212
Then we can plan our strategy.

00:46:59.588 --> 00:47:00.631
I'm sorry.

00:47:01.257 --> 00:47:02.508
It was too unreasonable.

00:47:03.300 --> 00:47:05.052
[sighs] I know.

00:47:05.511 --> 00:47:07.471
But this isn't the time for it.

00:47:07.555 --> 00:47:08.806
Then,

00:47:09.849 --> 00:47:11.267
what do you think we should do?

00:47:12.601 --> 00:47:13.602
[sighs]

00:47:14.937 --> 00:47:17.064
We'll just have to give in to her demands.

00:47:17.940 --> 00:47:20.443
We should start
by laying off all management levels,

00:47:20.526 --> 00:47:22.319
and quickly sell off the factories

00:47:22.820 --> 00:47:24.572
and other real estate to secure cash.

00:47:25.823 --> 00:47:27.074
It'll be quite a loss, but...

00:47:38.419 --> 00:47:39.670
It's as we expected.

00:47:40.921 --> 00:47:42.465
They pretended to be strangers.

00:47:42.965 --> 00:47:44.550
They're trying to sell it off dirt cheap

00:47:44.633 --> 00:47:46.302
and turn it into an empty shell.

00:47:47.094 --> 00:47:50.014
Then they'll sell
the proprietary technology and the brand.

00:47:50.473 --> 00:47:51.515
This is frustrating.

00:47:51.599 --> 00:47:53.392
Can't we just expose them?

00:47:53.476 --> 00:47:55.603
Let everyone know about their affair

00:47:55.686 --> 00:47:57.104
and their plan for take over.

00:47:57.188 --> 00:48:00.774
But adultery can't be used
as decisive evidence.

00:48:01.484 --> 00:48:04.778
We need concrete proof
that they conspired to commit fraud.

00:48:05.863 --> 00:48:08.991
We can't access their phones or accounts
by reporting their adultery.

00:48:09.074 --> 00:48:11.410
And if they insist
they're unrelated work-wise,

00:48:11.494 --> 00:48:12.786
it won't get us anywhere.

00:48:13.787 --> 00:48:15.956
[inhales deeply, exhales]

00:48:17.750 --> 00:48:20.085
I wish the chairwoman
would regain her consciousness.

00:48:22.213 --> 00:48:23.255
[sighs]

00:48:25.132 --> 00:48:26.634
[heart monitor beeps steadily]

00:48:30.804 --> 00:48:31.931
[Miyeon] Mom.

00:48:32.932 --> 00:48:35.142
Please wake up.

00:48:36.101 --> 00:48:39.146
[crying] Wake up
so that I can tell you I'm sorry.

00:48:40.105 --> 00:48:43.609
Why do you always make me the bad person?

00:48:44.860 --> 00:48:45.945
[sniffles]

00:48:48.906 --> 00:48:51.283
Mom, please wake up.

00:48:52.743 --> 00:48:53.911
[sniffling]

00:48:53.994 --> 00:48:56.080
[sobbing] I'm sorry.

00:48:56.664 --> 00:48:58.332
Wake up.

00:49:02.294 --> 00:49:03.712
[Miyeon continues sobbing]

00:49:06.131 --> 00:49:07.132
What?

00:49:07.800 --> 00:49:09.385
Grandma woke up?

00:49:09.468 --> 00:49:10.970
[♪ tense, dramatic music playing]

00:49:12.680 --> 00:49:13.722
[sighs softly]

00:49:14.223 --> 00:49:15.558
Okay, Mom.

00:49:15.641 --> 00:49:17.560
I'll head to the hospital now.

00:49:19.186 --> 00:49:20.271
[elevator chimes]

00:49:31.615 --> 00:49:32.866
[Jessica] One, two, three.

00:49:33.367 --> 00:49:34.493
Mine.

00:49:35.035 --> 00:49:36.036
[chuckles]

00:49:36.620 --> 00:49:38.163
[in English] It's my turn, Mommy.

00:49:41.041 --> 00:49:42.293
One, two. [gasps]

00:49:42.376 --> 00:49:43.419
You took two?

00:49:43.502 --> 00:49:45.379
My turn. Watch.

00:49:45.462 --> 00:49:46.547
One...

00:49:46.630 --> 00:49:47.673
Hold on.

00:49:49.550 --> 00:49:50.551
Hello?

00:49:54.263 --> 00:49:55.598
She woke up?

00:49:57.474 --> 00:49:58.559
[sighs softly]

00:49:58.642 --> 00:50:00.311
[♪ ominous music playing]

00:50:06.358 --> 00:50:07.401
VIP
KO PHILNYUN

00:50:42.102 --> 00:50:43.771
[Hangu] That old hag knows everything.

00:50:43.854 --> 00:50:45.230
We need to get rid of her now.

00:50:59.662 --> 00:51:01.163
[♪ music increases in tempo]

00:51:14.510 --> 00:51:16.053
-[gasps, yelps]
-[grunts]

00:51:17.221 --> 00:51:18.222
[grunts] Let me go!

00:51:18.764 --> 00:51:19.807
[grunts]

00:51:20.391 --> 00:51:21.433
[grunts, gasps]

00:51:21.725 --> 00:51:22.768
[panting]

00:51:25.437 --> 00:51:26.980
[yelps]

00:51:27.398 --> 00:51:28.524
[screams, grunts]

00:51:29.358 --> 00:51:30.859
[grunting] Let me go!

00:51:32.403 --> 00:51:35.072
-[yelps]
-[both panting]

00:51:35.155 --> 00:51:36.156
Oh Minjeong.

00:51:36.240 --> 00:51:37.241
[panting]

00:51:38.158 --> 00:51:39.535
[both grunting]

00:51:41.036 --> 00:51:42.037
[Jessica] No...

00:51:42.413 --> 00:51:43.831
No.

00:51:43.914 --> 00:51:45.040
Ms. Oh Minjeong.

00:51:45.124 --> 00:51:47.543
-You're under arrest for attempted murder.
-No.

00:51:47.626 --> 00:51:49.294
-No.
-You have the right to remain silent,

00:51:49.378 --> 00:51:50.546
the right to an attorney,

00:51:50.629 --> 00:51:52.840
and the right to request
a review of your arrest.

00:51:52.923 --> 00:51:54.383
-[Jessica] No!
-[officer] Take her away.

00:51:54.466 --> 00:51:55.926
[Jessica grunts, yelps]

00:51:57.177 --> 00:51:58.387
Let me go, damn it.

00:51:59.179 --> 00:52:00.180
Let go!

00:52:00.264 --> 00:52:01.932
[♪ music crescendos]

00:52:03.726 --> 00:52:05.018
It hurts.

00:52:13.485 --> 00:52:16.238
[Kim Wooju] We can't access their phones
or accounts by reporting them.

00:52:16.321 --> 00:52:18.323
And if they insist
they're unrelated to work,

00:52:18.407 --> 00:52:19.408
it'd be no use.

00:52:20.117 --> 00:52:22.494
I wish the chairwoman
would regain her consciousness.

00:52:23.120 --> 00:52:24.121
[sighs]

00:52:26.790 --> 00:52:27.791
[gasps softly]

00:52:28.751 --> 00:52:31.879
Let's make her wake up.

00:52:32.880 --> 00:52:34.923
Then the guilty one will come forward,

00:52:35.007 --> 00:52:36.925
the one who's afraid of her waking up.

00:52:37.676 --> 00:52:39.803
Catch that person

00:52:39.887 --> 00:52:41.847
to get access
to their phones and accounts.

00:52:43.265 --> 00:52:45.934
To do that, we need help from this person.

00:52:48.312 --> 00:52:49.772
[Eungsoo] What? Sylvia Oh?

00:52:50.564 --> 00:52:52.691
[Kim Wooju] I'm sorry to tell you this,

00:52:52.775 --> 00:52:55.235
but I'm sure of the relationship
between her and Uncle.

00:52:55.319 --> 00:52:58.113
And that woman is also related
to J Consulting in the US--

00:52:58.197 --> 00:52:59.448
Stop there.

00:52:59.865 --> 00:53:00.908
You knew?

00:53:03.452 --> 00:53:04.578
[sighs softly]

00:53:04.661 --> 00:53:07.748
I already knew Dad had a woman.

00:53:08.123 --> 00:53:09.750
I also knew that she was in the US.

00:53:09.833 --> 00:53:10.876
But... [sighs]

00:53:11.710 --> 00:53:13.295
I didn't know that was Sylvia Oh.

00:53:18.926 --> 00:53:21.053
I'm sure this is a lot to take in.

00:53:23.013 --> 00:53:24.181
There's another problem.

00:53:25.766 --> 00:53:28.811
Uncle and that woman
are planning to sell the company.

00:53:28.894 --> 00:53:30.312
[♪ tense, dramatic music playing]

00:53:31.730 --> 00:53:34.441
But you don't have any proof.
This is just your guess.

00:53:34.525 --> 00:53:37.027
Exactly, and I need your help
to find proof.

00:53:37.694 --> 00:53:39.696
To protect Grandma, the company,

00:53:40.572 --> 00:53:42.366
and even Auntie...

00:53:47.329 --> 00:53:48.872
[sighs] What do I have to do?

00:53:50.958 --> 00:53:52.626
[♪ stealthy music playing]

00:54:01.510 --> 00:54:02.678
What?

00:54:03.262 --> 00:54:04.847
Grandma woke up?

00:54:07.015 --> 00:54:08.016
[elevator button beeps]

00:54:08.392 --> 00:54:09.434
[sighs softly]

00:54:10.143 --> 00:54:11.311
Okay, Mom.

00:54:11.395 --> 00:54:13.438
I'll head to the hospital now.

00:54:14.398 --> 00:54:15.482
[elevator chimes]

00:54:20.779 --> 00:54:21.780
[sighs wearily]

00:54:24.825 --> 00:54:26.285
[♪ music crescendos, fades]

00:54:35.794 --> 00:54:36.879
Watch her head.

00:54:36.962 --> 00:54:40.591
[Meri] Ms. Oh Minjeong came,
not Director Jang.

00:54:41.049 --> 00:54:43.260
[Kim Wooju] Someone's been caught,
and it's just the start.

00:54:44.261 --> 00:54:47.598
Once they investigate her,
they'll find out who she's involved with.

00:54:49.641 --> 00:54:51.268
[siren wailing]

00:54:58.567 --> 00:54:59.818
Good work.

00:55:01.153 --> 00:55:02.696
I'm sure it was tough for you.

00:55:05.032 --> 00:55:06.491
You did well, too.

00:55:08.160 --> 00:55:09.453
Aren't you hungry?

00:55:09.536 --> 00:55:10.996
Do you want to go eat something?

00:55:11.872 --> 00:55:12.873
Sure.

00:55:16.543 --> 00:55:18.128
What do you want to eat?

00:55:18.462 --> 00:55:19.755
[hums thoughtfully]

00:55:21.548 --> 00:55:23.216
-Spicy stir-fried pork?
-[chuckles]

00:55:24.718 --> 00:55:27.596
At a hospital in Seoul,
BQ Capital CEO, Oh Minjeong,

00:55:27.679 --> 00:55:29.097
was arrested for attempting

00:55:29.181 --> 00:55:31.433
to poison Myungsoondang's chairwoman
Ko Philnyun.

00:55:31.516 --> 00:55:34.269
According to the police,
early yesterday morning,

00:55:34.353 --> 00:55:37.648
Ms. Oh infiltrated the chairwoman's
VIP hospital room,

00:55:37.731 --> 00:55:39.733
in an attempt to drug her.

00:55:39.816 --> 00:55:41.193
[reporter 1] With the forged contract,

00:55:41.276 --> 00:55:43.695
Myungsoondang was accused
of investment fraud.

00:55:43.779 --> 00:55:45.113
But the police has confirmed

00:55:45.197 --> 00:55:47.282
that Myungsoondang
was essentially the victim.

00:55:47.366 --> 00:55:49.743
[reporter 2] Police found evidence
from Ms. Oh's phone and emails

00:55:49.826 --> 00:55:53.455
indicating that she conspired
with a former executive of the Kaltz Hotel

00:55:53.538 --> 00:55:55.999
to forge the contract
and carry out the fraud.

00:55:56.083 --> 00:55:58.085
The police are now
cooperating with Interpol...

00:55:58.168 --> 00:56:00.504
I've told them already.

00:56:00.587 --> 00:56:03.131
I told them the chairwoman
would never do such a thing.

00:56:03.215 --> 00:56:05.801
But young people these days
aren't loyal to the company.

00:56:05.884 --> 00:56:08.220
They tried to send in resumes
to other companies,

00:56:08.303 --> 00:56:09.471
so I gave them an earful.

00:56:10.013 --> 00:56:13.892
I told them they shouldn't be
so disloyal to the company.

00:56:13.975 --> 00:56:14.976
[chuckles awkwardly]

00:56:17.437 --> 00:56:18.730
Oh, hey, guys. [chuckles]

00:56:19.106 --> 00:56:20.524
When did they get here?

00:56:20.607 --> 00:56:21.692
Ms. Oh...

00:56:22.401 --> 00:56:23.902
What a traitor.

00:56:23.985 --> 00:56:26.488
-Do you know how hard--
-We can do this!

00:56:26.571 --> 00:56:28.323
Let's work hard. Let's go!

00:56:31.702 --> 00:56:32.744
[Wonseok clears throat]

00:56:35.580 --> 00:56:36.581
Thank you, all of you.

00:56:37.874 --> 00:56:39.292
For believing in the company.

00:56:39.918 --> 00:56:43.171
I think we were able to get through
this crisis thanks to you.

00:56:43.255 --> 00:56:47.134
I'm sure you had it the toughest, Mr. Kim.
[chuckles softly]

00:56:48.385 --> 00:56:49.928
What's happening now, then?

00:56:50.011 --> 00:56:52.973
I heard a rumor
that Director Jang was involved.

00:56:53.890 --> 00:56:56.184
Sejung, I told you that was a secret.

00:56:57.310 --> 00:56:58.395
[whispers] Was it a secret?

00:56:58.478 --> 00:56:59.896
[Wonseok whispers] Didn't I tell you?

00:56:59.980 --> 00:57:02.149
[Sejung] I thought everyone
on the team knew.

00:57:03.191 --> 00:57:04.276
[phone vibrating]

00:57:05.026 --> 00:57:07.571
JUNGMUN POLICE STATION, DETECTIVE PARK

00:57:08.864 --> 00:57:10.949
[Det. Park] From the forensic analysis
of Ms. Oh's phone,

00:57:11.032 --> 00:57:13.326
we found evidence
that she conspired with David.

00:57:14.661 --> 00:57:18.165
But there were no personal texts
between her and Mr. Jang Hangu.

00:57:18.582 --> 00:57:21.084
There were also
no transactions to Mr. Jang's account.

00:57:22.169 --> 00:57:23.170
Really?

00:57:24.588 --> 00:57:26.715
She doesn't know anyone in Seoul,

00:57:26.798 --> 00:57:28.467
I had no choice but to come.

00:57:32.596 --> 00:57:34.055
[sighs, clicks tongue]

00:57:34.139 --> 00:57:35.849
It's not like you did anything wrong.

00:57:36.975 --> 00:57:38.101
Eat slowly.

00:57:38.185 --> 00:57:39.269
Okay.

00:57:39.936 --> 00:57:41.104
[in English] It's so yummy.

00:57:41.188 --> 00:57:42.189
[laughs]

00:57:43.899 --> 00:57:45.942
Put that down when you're eating.

00:57:46.443 --> 00:57:47.527
No.

00:57:47.611 --> 00:57:48.820
[in Korean] No.

00:57:49.237 --> 00:57:51.198
He's eating with me.

00:57:52.699 --> 00:57:53.867
Fine.

00:57:54.910 --> 00:57:57.370
I guess eating alone can get lonely.

00:57:57.829 --> 00:57:59.206
-Eat together then.
-[giggles]

00:58:00.040 --> 00:58:01.625
[in English] You want to eat some, too?

00:58:05.754 --> 00:58:09.549
I asked a restaurant manager
I used to work with to look after him.

00:58:10.509 --> 00:58:12.844
I only asked her
to help me out for a few days.

00:58:12.928 --> 00:58:14.429
So, please look after Henry.

00:58:14.513 --> 00:58:15.931
Don't worry.

00:58:17.432 --> 00:58:19.935
You deleted all the records
from the server, right?

00:58:21.269 --> 00:58:22.270
Yes.

00:58:23.271 --> 00:58:26.066
I also got rid of the phone
that I used to contact you.

00:58:27.150 --> 00:58:28.527
You did great. [chuckles]

00:58:29.444 --> 00:58:31.321
Someone's got to look after Henry.

00:58:32.030 --> 00:58:33.532
What did the lawyer say?

00:58:34.324 --> 00:58:36.785
They said you'll get about 15 years.

00:58:36.868 --> 00:58:39.746
But I'll use the best lawyer
to get you out as soon as possible.

00:58:43.875 --> 00:58:47.462
All you need to do is just remain silent.

00:58:48.255 --> 00:58:49.422
You'll get a divorce

00:58:50.549 --> 00:58:53.093
and take Henry to the US, right?

00:58:54.678 --> 00:58:55.887
[♪ tense music playing]

00:58:56.388 --> 00:58:57.389
Of course.

00:58:59.140 --> 00:59:00.141
Don't worry.

00:59:02.394 --> 00:59:04.771
[♪ dramatic sting, music fades]

00:59:21.079 --> 00:59:23.498
What brings you by without calling ahead?

00:59:23.582 --> 00:59:25.041
Are you coming from somewhere?

00:59:25.125 --> 00:59:27.502
Oh, I had a meeting outside.

00:59:27.586 --> 00:59:30.005
Not from a meeting
with Ms. Oh Minjeong, are you?

00:59:30.088 --> 00:59:31.464
[♪ gripping, tense music playing]

00:59:36.052 --> 00:59:37.053
What are you saying?

00:59:37.554 --> 00:59:40.015
I know of your relationship.

00:59:41.433 --> 00:59:42.517
That you lied to us

00:59:42.601 --> 00:59:45.312
to embezzle company funds
through J Consulting.

00:59:46.521 --> 00:59:47.522
[scoffs softly]

00:59:48.148 --> 00:59:49.774
And that you have a son in the US.

00:59:51.735 --> 00:59:52.944
Uncle,

00:59:53.403 --> 00:59:55.655
I'll expose everything

00:59:55.739 --> 00:59:58.617
that you've conspired
with Ms. Oh Minjeong.

01:00:01.620 --> 01:00:03.079
I was blackmailed.

01:00:05.957 --> 01:00:07.626
I had no choice.

01:00:08.251 --> 01:00:10.503
I was being dragged around by her threats.

01:00:10.587 --> 01:00:13.590
She said she wouldn't just sit back
if I didn't get the money.

01:00:13.673 --> 01:00:16.635
She also said the child is mine,
but I'm not really sure.

01:00:17.761 --> 01:00:18.929
I'm also scared.

01:00:21.598 --> 01:00:22.641
Believe me.

01:00:23.391 --> 01:00:25.852
Aside from the private contract
with J Consulting,

01:00:26.561 --> 01:00:29.314
I had nothing to do with BQ Capital.

01:00:29.397 --> 01:00:31.066
[♪ dramatic sting]

01:00:36.071 --> 01:00:37.072
[Eungsoo scoffs]

01:00:38.073 --> 01:00:39.074
Is that what he said?

01:00:40.951 --> 01:00:41.952
Yes.

01:00:44.287 --> 01:00:45.372
[sighs in exasperation]

01:00:46.081 --> 01:00:47.082
[scoffs]

01:00:50.835 --> 01:00:51.962
[sighs wearily]

01:00:59.970 --> 01:01:02.055
I'm not sure if this would help,

01:01:02.514 --> 01:01:03.848
but it'd at least prove

01:01:03.932 --> 01:01:06.142
that their relationship
wasn't based on a threat.

01:01:06.643 --> 01:01:08.478
[♪ suspenseful music playing]

01:01:14.067 --> 01:01:16.820
[Eungsoo] Back when I was 20,
on my way back home,

01:01:16.903 --> 01:01:19.572
I saw Dad secretly being
on the phone in the car.

01:01:19.656 --> 01:01:22.659
He was on the phone
every night in secret for hours.

01:01:23.451 --> 01:01:25.245
I wondered what it was about.

01:01:25.620 --> 01:01:27.539
So, I listened to the dash cam recordings.

01:01:29.374 --> 01:01:31.960
[Hangu] I'm going to New York next week
regarding Wooju's school.

01:01:32.043 --> 01:01:33.461
It's a tight schedule,

01:01:33.545 --> 01:01:35.505
so why don't you come to New York?

01:01:36.256 --> 01:01:37.257
[mouse clicks]

01:01:38.091 --> 01:01:39.134
Are you mad?

01:01:39.551 --> 01:01:42.512
I'll reserve your favorite restaurant
in New York.

01:01:43.346 --> 01:01:44.431
I miss you, too.

01:01:45.807 --> 01:01:47.225
[♪ tense music playing]

01:01:49.144 --> 01:01:50.186
[sighs softly]

01:01:50.270 --> 01:01:52.605
This isn't enough to prove embezzlement

01:01:53.106 --> 01:01:55.775
and the attempted murder of my grandma.

01:01:59.904 --> 01:02:01.031
[sighs wearily]

01:02:32.145 --> 01:02:35.690
Why did you try to kill Grandma?

01:02:41.988 --> 01:02:43.198
Should I tell you?

01:02:45.158 --> 01:02:47.452
Even without killing her,

01:02:48.161 --> 01:02:50.705
you could legally take over Myungsoondang.

01:02:51.956 --> 01:02:54.626
But why did you try to murder her?

01:02:59.339 --> 01:03:00.507
Perhaps Grandma knew

01:03:01.424 --> 01:03:04.886
that you and Jang Hangu
conspired together.

01:03:10.183 --> 01:03:11.226
I...

01:03:12.352 --> 01:03:13.895
I don't know

01:03:15.021 --> 01:03:16.815
Jang Hangu personally.

01:03:17.273 --> 01:03:18.525
Ms. Oh.

01:03:20.276 --> 01:03:22.278
I think you're trying to take the fall.

01:03:23.321 --> 01:03:25.615
But do you think Jang Hangu
will keep his promise?

01:03:29.994 --> 01:03:31.454
[Hangu] I had no choice.

01:03:31.913 --> 01:03:33.873
I was being dragged around by her threats.

01:03:33.957 --> 01:03:36.334
She wouldn't just sit back
if I didn't get the money.

01:03:36.417 --> 01:03:39.462
She also said the child is mine,
but I'm not really sure.

01:03:39.838 --> 01:03:41.005
I'm also scared.

01:03:41.089 --> 01:03:42.549
[♪ tense, dramatic music playing]

01:03:43.675 --> 01:03:46.970
Jang Hangu is already trying
to abandon you and your child.

01:03:49.597 --> 01:03:50.849
So, think carefully

01:03:51.516 --> 01:03:53.143
if you want to protect your son.

01:03:56.521 --> 01:03:57.605
[Jessica] Promise me...

01:04:00.400 --> 01:04:01.985
Henry's safety.

01:04:02.861 --> 01:04:04.112
[breath trembling]

01:04:04.195 --> 01:04:05.321
Then,

01:04:06.698 --> 01:04:08.116
I'll give you what you want.

01:04:08.741 --> 01:04:09.868
[sighs softly]

01:04:16.124 --> 01:04:18.126
The proof that you conspired
with Jang Hangu.

01:04:19.919 --> 01:04:20.920
Where is it?

01:04:22.046 --> 01:04:23.214
[breath trembling]

01:04:27.677 --> 01:04:29.262
CFO
JANG HANGU

01:04:30.054 --> 01:04:32.765
[Jessica] Just because I got rid
of the server and the phone,

01:04:32.849 --> 01:04:33.975
don't think you're safe.

01:04:35.018 --> 01:04:36.519
Because that's not everything.

01:04:37.478 --> 01:04:38.855
Don't forget.

01:04:38.938 --> 01:04:41.566
We got on the same boat 25 years ago,

01:04:41.649 --> 01:04:45.695
and neither of us can get off it first.

01:04:48.823 --> 01:04:50.950
"That's not everything..."

01:04:51.034 --> 01:04:52.744
[♪ music increases in tempo]

01:05:05.840 --> 01:05:07.050
[bag unzips]

01:05:07.133 --> 01:05:08.468
[♪ ominous music playing]

01:05:23.816 --> 01:05:25.109
[exclaims in annoyance]

01:05:31.241 --> 01:05:32.242
[grunts]

01:05:36.871 --> 01:05:38.039
[exclaims in frustration]

01:05:44.045 --> 01:05:45.213
[panting]

01:05:55.390 --> 01:05:56.641
[♪ music crescendos]

01:06:01.271 --> 01:06:02.647
[Henry in English] Mommy, wait.

01:06:06.276 --> 01:06:08.111
[chuckles] Look at him.

01:06:08.569 --> 01:06:11.531
He always takes that with him
because it's a gift from you.

01:06:11.948 --> 01:06:12.949
[chuckles]

01:06:25.712 --> 01:06:26.754
[object clicks]

01:06:28.506 --> 01:06:29.882
[♪ tense, foreboding music playing]

01:06:41.436 --> 01:06:42.979
[♪ music increases in tempo]

01:06:45.732 --> 01:06:46.816
[scoffs]

01:06:51.696 --> 01:06:52.697
[sighs softly]

01:06:55.116 --> 01:06:56.576
[cell phone powers on]

01:06:57.744 --> 01:06:59.704
[Hangu] You go ahead to Unit 401.

01:06:59.787 --> 01:07:01.372
I'll leave when my wife is asleep.

01:07:01.456 --> 01:07:02.790
My brother-in-law noticed.

01:07:02.874 --> 01:07:04.334
We'll have to be careful.

01:07:04.417 --> 01:07:05.918
Of course, I miss you, too.

01:07:06.002 --> 01:07:08.171
Just wait until everything is finished.

01:07:08.254 --> 01:07:09.422
Don't be anxious.

01:07:09.505 --> 01:07:10.923
Just trust me.

01:07:11.007 --> 01:07:12.759
Everything will go as planned.

01:07:15.345 --> 01:07:17.305
THEY JUST LEFT
PLATE NUMBER SEOUL 10 NI 3309

01:07:21.142 --> 01:07:22.185
They just left.

01:07:22.268 --> 01:07:24.604
25 YEARS AGO

01:07:24.687 --> 01:07:28.983
The plate number is Seoul 10 Ni 3309.

01:07:34.113 --> 01:07:35.156
[Miyeon] Honey.

01:07:36.908 --> 01:07:37.992
What are you doing?

01:07:38.076 --> 01:07:39.327
Come have some fruit.

01:07:39.410 --> 01:07:40.620
Okay, I'm on my way.

01:07:40.703 --> 01:07:41.996
[both chuckle]

01:07:42.080 --> 01:07:43.373
I looked everywhere for you.

01:07:45.792 --> 01:07:47.502
THEY JUST LEFT
PLATE: SEOUL 10 NI 3309

01:07:47.585 --> 01:07:49.045
[♪ tense, foreboding music continues]

01:07:52.298 --> 01:07:53.508
UNDER CONSTRUCTION
NO ENTRY

01:07:53.591 --> 01:07:54.801
NO ENTRY

01:08:02.892 --> 01:08:05.061
-There must be a construction site.
-I guess so.

01:08:06.813 --> 01:08:08.523
SEOUL 10 NI 3309

01:08:19.033 --> 01:08:20.451
Are you still upset, Wooju?

01:08:20.535 --> 01:08:24.956
It was my birthday present.
Why did you give it to Eungsoo?

01:08:25.039 --> 01:08:26.749
It was mine.

01:08:26.833 --> 01:08:29.043
He wanted it.

01:08:29.127 --> 01:08:31.838
His whole family came
to wish you a happy birthday.

01:08:31.921 --> 01:08:34.006
-Couldn't you give him that?
-No.

01:08:34.882 --> 01:08:37.969
He always takes what's mine.

01:08:38.594 --> 01:08:40.263
He's a mean pig.

01:08:40.346 --> 01:08:43.182
You can't talk like that
about your cousin.

01:08:43.266 --> 01:08:44.559
Take it back.

01:08:53.276 --> 01:08:54.735
Or Dad will get really angry.

01:08:55.194 --> 01:08:56.279
You won't take it back?

01:08:58.656 --> 01:09:01.659
You're a good boy, aren't you?
Do as your dad says.

01:09:02.785 --> 01:09:03.786
[exclaims]

01:09:04.537 --> 01:09:05.746
You won't take it back?

01:09:06.622 --> 01:09:07.999
[Kim Wooju's dad sighs]

01:09:08.291 --> 01:09:11.919
Then I won't buy you the toy robot.

01:09:19.802 --> 01:09:20.845
[gasps] Honey!

01:09:20.928 --> 01:09:22.138
[truck horn blaring]

01:09:23.306 --> 01:09:24.974
-[all scream]
-[horn blaring]

01:09:25.057 --> 01:09:26.934
[tires screeching]

01:09:39.489 --> 01:09:40.907
[♪ ominous music playing]

01:09:51.542 --> 01:09:53.794
I TOOK CARE OF IT

01:09:58.966 --> 01:10:00.843
[exclaims smugly] This was it.

01:10:11.437 --> 01:10:12.605
-[sighs softly]
-[laptop chimes]

01:10:14.106 --> 01:10:16.359
PHONE RECORDINGS

01:10:16.442 --> 01:10:17.902
[♪ music increases in tempo]

01:10:29.121 --> 01:10:32.124
[Jessica] The president
found out about us.

01:10:32.583 --> 01:10:33.626
What do we do?

01:10:33.709 --> 01:10:35.044
[Hangu] We need to get rid of him.

01:10:35.127 --> 01:10:36.128
[Jessica] What?

01:10:36.212 --> 01:10:38.506
[Hangu] There's a family gathering
in Yeosu next week.

01:10:38.589 --> 01:10:41.676
That's when we'll have to get it done.

01:10:53.187 --> 01:10:54.188
[whistling tune]

01:10:55.106 --> 01:10:56.440
[♪ dramatic sting]

01:11:17.670 --> 01:11:18.838
Was it you, Uncle?

01:11:22.758 --> 01:11:23.759
Tell me.

01:11:25.928 --> 01:11:27.138
Was it you?

01:11:27.221 --> 01:11:28.598
[♪ tense, foreboding music playing]

01:11:37.732 --> 01:11:38.816
[♪ ethereal sparkle]

01:11:38.900 --> 01:11:40.443
[♪ dreamy pop music playing]

01:11:47.283 --> 01:11:49.911
THANKS TO KIM MINSANG
FOR THE SPECIAL APPEARANCE

01:12:05.384 --> 01:12:08.054
WOULD YOU MARRY ME?

01:12:08.137 --> 01:12:09.680
[Kim Wooju] He asked me for forgiveness,

01:12:09.764 --> 01:12:10.890
but he killed my parents.

01:12:10.973 --> 01:12:13.017
[judge] The nature
of the crime is heinous,

01:12:13.100 --> 01:12:14.685
-and its social harm is substantial.
-[Hangu screaming]

01:12:14.769 --> 01:12:17.480
Accordingly, this court hereby
grants the defendant...

01:12:17.563 --> 01:12:19.106
[Jingyeong] She regained
her consciousness.

01:12:19.190 --> 01:12:20.775
[Meri] Let's meet at home.

01:12:20.858 --> 01:12:24.153
I don't think we can accept
the house that I won through the raffle.

01:12:24.236 --> 01:12:26.697
Well, this really feels
like we're newlyweds.

01:12:26.781 --> 01:12:27.865
[Kim Wooju] We are newlyweds.

01:12:27.949 --> 01:12:29.784
-My heart...
-[Sejung] Let's buy some fruit.

01:12:29.867 --> 01:12:31.577
[Eunsook] Didn't you know
she's a divorcée?

01:12:31.661 --> 01:12:33.955
-[Youngsook] Let's end this together!
-[Wooju's sister] No, stop!

01:12:34.038 --> 01:12:35.247
[Sori screams]

01:12:35.331 --> 01:12:36.624
[Jingyeong] Why don't you call me

01:12:37.124 --> 01:12:38.125
once a week?

01:12:38.960 --> 01:12:40.211
[Wooju] Just wait.

01:12:40.294 --> 01:12:41.587
I'm still here.

01:12:41.671 --> 01:12:42.964
[Meri] Something happened, Wooju.

01:12:43.047 --> 01:12:44.715
A woman, my current legal wife,

01:12:44.799 --> 01:12:45.841
Yoo Meri.

01:12:45.967 --> 01:12:47.051
[Kim Wooju] What?

01:12:47.134 --> 01:12:48.219
A press conference?

01:12:50.721 --> 01:12:52.723
Translated by Susanna Kim